Installing cockpit   (in this order)

1.) sudo apt install cockpit -y

2.) sudo systemctl enable --now cockpit.socket

You should now be able to goto htt:(server_ip):9090  to access the application

Next you will need to update you network config to have it appear in this application.

1.) cd /etc/netplan
2.) sudo nano 50-cloud-init.yaml
    network:
    version: 2
    renderer: NetworkManager   (Add this line)

3.) save change and exit out.
4.) sudo netplan try (should get no errors)
